The paper deals with stability and convergence of stochastic approximation algorithms, which are commonly used in reinforcement learning (RL) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also specifically mentions temporal difference learning (TD), which is a popular method in RL. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
